<font color="#FF0000">PROTESTER</font><br>
<tt>Sat Feb  8 20:05:00 US/Eastern 1997
</tt><p>
Arthur asks a good question which is what would you have done if there had been no Vietnam War? I would have had more time to be involved in other causes, such as civil rights, and calling for nuclear disarmament. I would have been on the forefront of the environmentalist movement. However, I admit that most protesters would not have been involved in politics at all. I admit that a small minority of protesters ,if there had been no war, would have devoted themselves entirely to marijuana, alcoholism, and promiscuity. One thing I could not stand was that some people calling themselves protesters had animosity towards those who fought in Vietnam. The whole premise of the protest movement was to end the war, and save the lives of the those in Vietnam. I was protesting on behalf of the American soldiers in Vietnam, to end the war, and save their lives. We were trying to bring them home. Also, about the Persian Gulf War, I think everyone agrees that George Bush would never have gone to war if there was no oil in Kuwait. Also, the form of government in Kuwait is hardly &quot;irrelevant&quot;. The people in Kuwait are still no free, because they are under the thumb of the Emir.
<p><code>--   (Sarah) </code><p>


